<2ND_LINE>PM-Quayle-Father,0116</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Father Says ``Booze And Broads'' Quote Misconstrued</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The father of Republican vice presidential
nominee Dan Quayle says a statement about his son's school
interests was misconstrued in a published report.
   James C. Quayle was quoted in a story Wednesday in the Daily
News of New York as saying his son's main interests in school were
``broads and booze.''
   The Indiana senator's father said Thursday he had intended the
statement as a reflection on himself.
   ```I said, `If he's anything like his old man, it was probably
broads and booze,''' Quayle told the Daily News in its report
Thursday. ``He (Dan) isn't that kind of guy.''
