<2ND_LINE>PM-Treasury Bills,100</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Interest on 52-Week T-Bills At Highest Level in Three Years</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Interest rates on 52-week Treasury bills have
risen to their highest level in more than three years.
   The Treasury Department announced Thursday that it sold $9
billion of the bills at an average discount rate of 7.72 percent,
up from 7.40 percent at the last auction on July 28.
   The rates were the highest since the one-year bills sold for
7.94 percent on May 14, 1985. The new discount rate understates the
actual return to investors _ 8.32 percent with a $10,000 bill
selling for $9,219.40.
