<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0417</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Rains Drench Desert Southwest</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Thunderstorm showers inundated areas from the southern Rockies
to the desert Southwest today after monsoon rains caused flash
flooding that washed out roads.
   In Arizona, strong thunderstorm rains drenched the Chino Valley
on Thursday afternoon, producing more than 2 inches of rain in just
30 minutes. Flash flooding was reported in the valley south of
Flagstaff and north of Phoenix, and streets were washed out.
   Mount Lemmon in southeast Arizona reported more than 2 inches of
rain.
   In New Mexico, showers and thunderstorms swept through much of
the state Thursday night. More than an inch of rain falling on
Albuquerque.
   In central Oklahoma, showers and thunderstorms developed late
Thursday. Winds gusted to 60 mph and were accompanied by
nickel-size hail.
   In the Northeast, showers were scattered along a cold front
extending from New York to western Pennsylvania and southwest Ohio.
   Today's forecast called for widespread showers and thunderstorms
through Florida; widespread showers through much of New England and
upper Michigan; scattered showers and thunderstorms through the
northern Plains and the central Rockies; and mostly sunny skies in
the rest of the nation.
   High temperatures were forecast in the 80s and 90s across much
of the nation; near 100 degree from the Rio Grande Valley to
central Texas and much of Oklahoma; between 100 and 110 degrees
from the desert Southwest to the California valleys; in the 70s
from northern New England to the Great Lakes, the upper Mississippi
Valley, North Dakota and northern Montana; and the 60s in northern
Michigan and northeast Minnesota.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 46
degrees at Bismarck, N.D., to 92 degrees at Phoenix.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 71 fair; Boston 67 foggy; Buffalo 58 fair;
Charleston, S.C. 76 foggy; Cincinnati 68 fair; Cleveland 58 fair;
Detroit 59 fair; Miami 81 fair; New York 67 fair; Philadelphia 69
fair; Pittsburgh 59 showery; Portland, Maine 63 foggy; Washington
68 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 44 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth 80 fair; Denver 68
fair; Des Moines 56 fair; Indianapolis 64 cloudy; Kansas City 62
fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 58 fair; Nashville 64 fair; New Orleans
74 foggy; St. Louis 71 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 67 cloudy; Anchorage 55 cloudy; Las Vegas 88
cloudy; Los Angeles 68 fair; Phoenix 91 partly cloudy; Salt Lake
City 74 fair; San Diego 71 fair; Seattle 60 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 61 cloudy; Toronto 55 fair.
</TEXT>
