<FILEID>AP-NR-08-26-88 1229EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Japan-Flood     08-26 0119</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Japan-Flood,0123</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>5,000 People Evacuated Due To Floods in Hokkaido</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three days of heavy rain caused a river in northern
Japan to overflow its banks Friday, flooding 6,000 houses and
forcing the evacuation of more than 5,000 people in surrounding
towns, an official said.
   No deaths were reported. The river is in Rumoi, on the western
coast of the northern island of Hokkaido.
   The evacuees were sent to schools and public halls, said a
spokesman for the Hokkaido police. He spoke on condition of
anonymity.
   The flooding damaged streets and bridges, the spokesman said.
Parts of six national highways and 32 other roads were closed.
   A spokesman for the railroad said 105 trains were canceled.
</TEXT>
