<HEAD>Desert Shaken By Quake; No Damage or Injuries</HEAD>
<DATELINE>YUCCA VALLEY, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A remote section of desert was
jolted by a slight earthquake that caused no damage or injuries,
authorities said Friday.
   The quake at 9:57 p.m. Thursday was centered about 100 miles
northeast of Los Angeles, said Janet Fernandez, a spokeswoman for
the California Institute of Technology.
   She said it measured 3.8 on the Richter scale of ground motion,
enough to cause slight damage in the local area. But no injuries or
damage were reported, said Karen Gemette, a San Bernardino County
fire spokeswoman in Yucca Valley, 27 miles south of the epicenter.
