<HEAD>Hydrofoil Rams Banks of Siberian River</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The alternate captain of a hydrofoil collapsed and
died at the controls as it cruised a Siberian river, and the vessel
ran aground at full speed, injuring 11 passengers and crew, Tass
reported Friday.
   The Raketa-15 slammed into the shore of the Irtysh River near
Omsk, 1,350 miles southeast of Moscow, the official Soviet news
agency said. The accident occured Thursday, Tass said without
explaining the reporting delay.
