<HEAD>Reagan Appoints Ambassador to Pakistan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan made a recess appointment
Friday of Robert B. Oakley as ambassador to the Islamic Republic of
Pakistan, the White House announced.
   Oakley is a career foreign service officer and has served as the
State Department's anti-terrorism chief.
