a plance explosion last week with Pakistani President Mohammad Zia
Ul-Haq.
   Secretary of State George Shultz traveled to Zia's funeral with
Oakley and introduced him as the designated man for the post.
   Reagan made the appointment while in California for his annual
summer vacation.
