<HEAD>Dukakis, Bentsen Win Nurses' Nod</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The American Nurses' Association on Friday
announced its endorsement of Democratic presidential nominee
Michael Dukakis, praising him as ``a strong supporter'' of women's
concerns.
   Association president Lucille Joel cited the Massachusetts
governor's health care record as a key reason for its backing of
Dukakis and his running mate, Sen. Lloyd Bentsen of Texas.
   ``In addition to being in the forefront on health care issues,
Dukakis is a strong supporter on key matters of concern to working
women,'' said Joel, noting Dukakis' support of affordable child
care, pay equity and civil rights.
   The American Nurses' Association represents 2 million registered
nurses nationwide.
