<HEAD>Quotes From the Presidential Campaign Trail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some comments Friday from the
presidential campaign trail:
   
   GEORGE BUSH, slamming Michael Dukakis for criticizing the Reagan
administration's drug efforts: ``He is the governor who vetoed the
mandatory sentencing for drug dealers. He opposes capital
punishment for drug kingpins. And he fought tooth and nail to keep
that outrageous furlough program that lets murderers, rapists and
drug dealers out on appeal.''
   
   MICHAEL DUKAKIS, applauding Bush's statement that deployment of
the ``Star Wars'' space defense system should be contingent on
further research: ``I think that makes sense. I'm glad to see that
the vice president now agrees with me and a great number of
American citizens.''
   
   DAN QUAYLE, saying he won't authorize the public release of his
academic records: ``I don't want you to go through and pore over
all those mediocre grades I got.''
   
   JESSE JACKSON, pledging to get out the vote for the Democratic
ticket: ``Bush and Quayle want to privatize the Justice Department.
They want to privatize foreign policy. They want to privatize
public education. And since they like privacy so much, I want to
help them move back into private life.''
   
   Sen. JOHN STENNIS, D-Miss., praising his colleague Lloyd Bentsen
during a campaign stop in Jackson: ``I was really thrilled when I
heard ... he was going to be the candidate for vice president. No
one there (in the Senate) excels him, and not too many equal him.''
