<HEAD>British Customs Officers Seize 1,600 Pounds Hashish</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HARWICH, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Customs officers making a random check
of a cattle truck arriving from the Netherlands Friday turned up
1,600 pounds of hashish worth $3.4 million, police said.
   The Dutch truck driver, Teunis Overweel, 32, appeared Friday in
Harwich Magistrate's Court and was charged with illegal importation
of drugs, said police in Harwich, a port city 71 miles northeast of
London.
   Overweel will be held in custody pending another court
appearance next Tuesday, said a police spokesman who demanded
anonymity.
   The truck was not carrying livestock. Police said the drug was
concealed in trays in the chassis.
   Police said they did not know Overweel's hometown.
