<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Chile-Quake     08-26 0103</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Chile-Quake,0105</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Tremor Shakes Northern Chile</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTIAGO, Chile (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A tremor shook northern Chile Friday, but
no damage or injuries were reported, authorities said.
   The Seismological Intitute of the University of Chile said the
tremor measured three on Mercalli scale and was centered 190 miles
north of Santiago, near the coastal city of La Serena.
   Police reported no damage or injuries.
   The Mercalli scale gauges the intensity of an earthquake as felt
in a specific location. The scale runs from 1 to 12: a 1 reading is
not felt except by very few, favorably situated. A 12 reading is
total damage.
</TEXT>
