<2ND_LINE>BC-Auto Prodn,0152</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Auto Production Up This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
201,190 cars and light trucks this week, up from last week's
182,212, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago,
in which 181,043 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 123,747 cars this week,
compared with 109,208 a week ago and 117,220 in the same week in
1987.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 77,443,
compared with last week's 73,004 and last year's 63,823.
   Canadian automakers were to build 20,818 cars this week, up from
16,562 a week ago and up from last year's 12,466.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 17,000,
compared with 19,205 a week ago and 15,773 in the same week last
year.
</TEXT>
