<HEAD>Production Company Agrees to Sell Pittsburgh TV Station</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CULVER CITY, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Lorimar Telepictures Corp. said
Friday it has agreed to sell WPGH-TV in Pittsburgh to the owner of
stations in Hartford, Conn., and Miami.
   Lorimar, best known as the producer of ``Dallas,'' ``Knots
Landing'' and other TV shows, said the independent UHF station
would be purchased by a group organized by Michael Finkelstein,
owner of WTXX-TV in Hartford and WDZL in Miami.
   The price wasn't disclosed. Lorimar bought WPGH in January 1987
for $21.2 million.
   The sale to Renaissance Communications, a company organized by
Finkelstein along with Warburg Pincus Capital, is subject to
regulatory approval and negotiation of a definitive agreement.
   Lorimar, which has agreed to be acquired by Warner
Communications Inc., has been selling some assets in recent months,
and WPGH is the fourth of its six small television stations to be
sold.
</TEXT>
